preparation_guide: 1. Preheat the oven to 180°C. 2. Mix the olive oil, garlic, and herbs in a bowl. 3. Marinate the chicken in the mixture for 30 minutes. 4. Place the chicken on a baking tray and bake for 25 minutes, or until golden brown.

name: Greek Salad with Feta
short_description: A nutritious option for any meal.
preparation_guide: 1. In a medium saucepan, heat olive oil over medium heat. 2. Add the onions and cook until softened, about 5 minutes. 3. Stir in the garlic and cook for an additional minute. 4. Add the tomatoes and broth, then bring to a simmer. 5. Let the soup simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

name: Pasta Primavera
short_description: A nutritious option for any meal.
preparation_guide: 1. Boil water in a large pot. 2. Add the pasta and cook for 10 minutes. 3. In a separate pan, sauté the vegetables with olive oil until tender. 4. Mix the pasta with the vegetables and season with salt and pepper. Serve hot.

ingredients: chicken breast, salt, butter, tomatoes, spinach
preparation_guide: 1. Preheat the oven to 180°C. 2. Mix the olive oil, garlic, and herbs in a bowl. 3. Marinate the chicken in the mixture for 30 minutes. 4. Place the chicken on a baking tray and bake for 25 minutes, or until golden brown.

name: Shrimp Tacos
short_description: A delicious and healthy meal perfect for lunch or dinner.
ingredients: spinach, potatoes, garlic, olive oil, salt, pork, cheese
preparation_guide: 1. In a medium saucepan, heat olive oil over medium heat. 2. Add the onions and cook until softened, about 5 minutes. 3. Stir in the garlic and cook for an additional minute. 4. Add the tomatoes and broth, then bring to a simmer. 5. Let the soup simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

name: Pasta Primavera
short_description: A hearty and filling meal to enjoy any day.
ingredients: onions, tomatoes, cheese, olive oil, garlic, potatoes, spinach
preparation_guide: 1. Preheat the oven to 200°C. 2. Roll out the pie crust and press it into a pie dish. 3. In a bowl, whisk together the eggs, milk, and cream. 4. Add the spinach and cheese to the egg mixture and pour into the pie crust. 5. Bake for 35 minutes, or until the quiche is set.

ingredients: spinach, cheese, potatoes, eggs, chicken breast
preparation_guide: 1. Boil water in a large pot. 2. Add the pasta and cook for 10 minutes. 3. In a separate pan, sauté the vegetables with olive oil until tender. 4. Mix the pasta with the vegetables and season with salt and pepper. Serve hot.

name: Pumpkin Pie
short_description: A nutritious option for any meal.
preparation_guide: 1. Heat the grill to medium heat. 2. Season the steak with salt, pepper, and garlic powder. 3. Grill the steak for 5-7 minutes on each side for medium-rare. 4. Let the steak rest for 5 minutes before slicing. Serve with a side of roasted vegetables.

name: Baked Salmon with Lemon
short_description: A savory dish that will satisfy your cravings.
ingredients: tomatoes, pork, onions, beef, carrots, olive oil
preparation_guide: 1. Preheat the oven to 200°C. 2. Roll out the pie crust and press it into a pie dish. 3. In a bowl, whisk together the eggs, milk, and cream. 4. Add the spinach and cheese to the egg mixture and pour into the pie crust. 5. Bake for 35 minutes, or until the quiche is set.

name: Lentil Soup

preparation_guide: 1. Boil water in a large pot. 2. Add the pasta and cook for 10 minutes. 3. In a separate pan, sauté the vegetables with olive oil until tender. 4. Mix the pasta with the vegetables and season with salt and pepper. Serve hot.

name: Shrimp Tacos
short_description: A quick and easy recipe full of flavor.
ingredients: milk, eggs, pork, tomatoes, cheese, salt
preparation_guide: 1. Preheat the oven to 180°C. 2. Mix the olive oil, garlic, and herbs in a bowl. 3. Marinate the chicken in the mixture for 30 minutes. 4. Place the chicken on a baking tray and bake for 25 minutes, or until golden brown.

name: Pasta Primavera
short_description: A quick and easy recipe full of flavor.
ingredients: carrots, garlic, chicken breast, pepper, tomatoes, onions, milk
preparation_guide: 1. Heat the grill to medium heat. 2. Season the steak with salt, pepper, and garlic powder. 3. Grill the steak for 5-7 minutes on each side for medium-rare. 4. Let the steak rest for 5 minutes before slicing. Serve with a side of roasted vegetables.

name: Classic Caesar Salad
short_description: A delicious and healthy meal perfect for lunch or dinner.
ingredients: potatoes, chicken breast, carrots, cheese, salt, pasta, onions
preparation_guide: 1. Preheat the oven to 200°C. 2. Roll out the pie crust and press it into a pie dish. 3. In a bowl, whisk together the eggs, milk, and cream. 4. Add the spinach and cheese to the egg mixture and pour into the pie crust. 5. Bake for 35 minutes, or until the quiche is set.

preparation_guide: 1. Preheat the oven to 180°C. 2. Mix the olive oil, garlic, and herbs in a bowl. 3. Marinate the chicken in the mixture for 30 minutes. 4. Place the chicken on a baking tray and bake for 25 minutes, or until golden brown.

name: Chicken Alfredo
short_description: A delicious and healthy meal perfect for lunch or dinner.
ingredients: olive oil, spinach, eggs, onions, pork, carrots

name: Tomato Basil Soup
